Abstract = {{We investigate the possibility of reducing the complexity of
   multireference perturbation theory through cumulant based approximations
   to the high-order density matrices that appear in such theories. Our
   test cases show that while the cumulant approximated forms are degraded
   in accuracy relative to the parent theory and exhibit intruder state
   problems that must be carefully handled, they may provide a route to a
   simple estimation of dynamic correlation when the parent perturbation
   theory is infeasible. Nonetheless, further work is clearly needed on
   better approximations to the denominators in the perturbation theory.}},
